from t-mobile.♪

08:25.982 --> 08:28.813
♪it only costs $50 bucks
at t-mobile.♪

08:29.648 --> 08:31.480
♪just one cord to set up.♪

08:31.482 --> 08:34.513
♪say goodbye to that truck.♪

08:34.515 --> 08:37.246
♪oh, what a beautiful
mornin'...♪

08:37.248 --> 08:39.946
♪oh, what a beautiful day...♪

08:41.115 --> 08:44.546
♪they won't raise your rates
at t-mobile...♪

08:44.548 --> 08:47.246
♪you'll get a great deal
every day!♪

08:47.248 --> 08:48.546
<i> Home internet from t-mobile...</i>

08:48.548 --> 08:49.846
<i> Just $50 bucks a month.</i>

09:25.840 --> 09:27.340
Peter, what are you doing here?

09:27.467 --> 09:29.091
You told me to get a job,
and they were hiring.

09:29.219 --> 09:30.051
I love it here!

09:30.178 --> 09:31.219
Plus, they let me joke around

09:31.304 --> 09:33.512
With the wells fargo guys
who work here.

09:33.598 --> 09:36.349
Yes, I'd like to make
a deposit, please.

09:36.434 --> 09:39.227
Is it another 100 grand
chocolate bar?

09:39.312 --> 09:41.187
Okay, so I've had you before.

09:41.231 --> 09:44.148
Peter, the grocery store is
kind of my domain.

09:44.234 --> 09:46.025
While I'm glad you got a job,

09:46.110 --> 09:47.944
I don't love
that you got one here.

09:48.029 --> 09:49.403
Don't worry.
You won't even know I'm here.

09:49.530 --> 09:50.947
Unless you're
near the front door,

09:51.032 --> 09:52.782
Which I can open
with the force.

09:52.867 --> 09:54.951
Excuse me,
where are the peanuts?

09:55.036 --> 09:56.369
Aisle seven.

09:56.496 --> 09:58.454
Peter, peanuts are on aisle two.

09:58.539 --> 09:59.705
Eh, I just tell 'em
whatever number,

09:59.791 --> 10:02.250
And then I disappear
into the produce mist.

10:04.003 --> 10:05.544
Peter? Peter?

10:05.630 --> 10:10.466
Peter (echoing):
There was never peter,
only loose carrots.

10:13.263 --> 10:16.222
The body was discovered
around 9:00 p.M.

10:16.349 --> 10:19.183
Unfortunately, I couldn't
make it down to the crime scene

10:19.269 --> 10:20.726
Because there were no ramps.

10:20.812 --> 10:22.186
Okay, I'm gonna write:

10:22.272 --> 10:24.146
"tonight,
all the streets in this town

10:24.232 --> 10:25.648
Were a dead end."

10:25.733 --> 10:27.191
I never saw the body.

10:27.235 --> 10:29.318
It was cold,
so they sent me on a coffee run.

10:29.445 --> 10:31.487
My lap can
accommodate two trays,

10:31.614 --> 10:33.072
And I can't feel the spills.

10:33.199 --> 10:36.158
"she was found in a creek,
her bosoms frozen solid."

10:36.244 --> 10:39.870
She was a heavyset 60-something
in welder's coveralls.

10:39.956 --> 10:42.373
"no one from beverly hills
had ever been strangled

10:42.458 --> 10:44.292
By their own cheerleader skirt
before."

10:44.419 --> 10:45.710
(gasps)

10:45.878 --> 10:48.713
Wow, I can't believe I'm seeing
how the sausage is made.

10:48.798 --> 10:52.216
Hey, so when you open a book
and you see "random house,"

10:52.302 --> 10:54.343
Is that something
we come up with?

10:54.387 --> 10:57.096
Uh, no, that's-that's
the publisher's name.

10:57.223 --> 10:59.307
I see.
Just drinking it all in.

10:59.392 --> 11:01.434
And what about the list of
cities you see under that name?

11:01.519 --> 11:04.895
Because I was thinking we should
put new york, paris, kokomo.

11:04.981 --> 11:07.315
Those are just the cities
where the publisher has offices.

11:07.400 --> 11:09.191
And kokomo isn't
a real city, joe.

11:09.319 --> 11:11.193
Try telling the beach boys that.

11:11.279 --> 11:13.696
I don't know what our title
should be yet, but beneath it,

11:13.781 --> 11:16.657
It should say: "soon to be
a major motion picture."

11:16.784 --> 11:18.951
I always buy the book
when I see that.

11:19.037 --> 11:20.453
Why don't we just focus
on the writing?

11:20.580 --> 11:21.912
Oh, hey, you ever see books

11:21.998 --> 11:23.914
Where the edges
of the pages are gold?

11:24.083 --> 11:26.459
-Yeah?
-So cool.

11:31.758 --> 11:33.174
What is going on in here?

11:33.259 --> 11:35.217
Who put price tags
on all the cans?

11:35.303 --> 11:37.553
And why is everything
labeled 69 cents?

11:37.680 --> 11:40.890
<i> Peter (muffled):</i>
<i> Griffin family grocery is</i>
<i> currently under renovation.</i>

11:41.059 --> 11:42.933
<i> Please excuse our dust.</i>

11:43.019 --> 11:44.643
Peter? Where are you?

11:44.729 --> 11:46.979
<i> Staring at butts</i>
<i> from behind a one-way mirror.</i>

11:47.065 --> 11:48.856
And why'd you
rearrange everything?

11:48.983 --> 11:50.483
I just want to find my vitamins.

11:50.610 --> 11:53.110
<i> Cupboard four.</i>
<i> No, that's cupboard seven.</i>

11:53.196 --> 11:54.820
<i> No, wrong way.</i>

11:54.906 --> 11:57.073
I'm not...
Is it warmer or colder?

11:57.158 --> 11:59.200
<i> Cupboard four.</i>
<i> Cupboard four.</i>

12:00.119 --> 12:01.660
(alarm blaring)

12:01.788 --> 12:04.080
Ma'am, don't worry,
this happens all the time.

12:04.248 --> 12:05.873
I'm sure you have your receipt.

12:05.958 --> 12:07.666
What? No,
I don't have a receipt.

12:07.752 --> 12:10.127
Okay, then, we're just gonna
go to the office,

12:10.296 --> 12:13.381
Call your parents,
and send you on your way.

12:14.926 --> 12:17.051
-Daddy, I just...
-There are gonna be
some changes around here.

12:17.136 --> 12:19.011
First off, no more lipstick.

12:19.097 --> 12:21.847
That's how
all this trouble started.

12:26.187 --> 12:27.269
Okay,
so we just need the ending.

12:27.355 --> 12:28.479
Who was the murderer?

12:28.564 --> 12:31.273
Oh, I have no idea.
It's a cold case.

12:31.359 --> 12:33.818
That's what makes 'em cold--
no one knows how to solve 'em.

12:33.903 --> 12:35.069
Well, how do we finish our novel

12:35.154 --> 12:37.530
If we don't know what happened
in real life?

12:37.615 --> 12:39.031
-Ghost cop.
-No.

12:39.117 --> 12:40.157
Do you know what this means?

12:40.284 --> 12:42.159
We're gonna put on
our sherlock holmes hats

12:42.328 --> 12:44.328
And solve the murder ourselves?

12:44.414 --> 12:46.789
Deerstalker hats, joe.
But yes.

12:46.874 --> 12:49.500
Stupid nonwriter!

12:52.338 --> 12:54.246
Okay, brian, now,
when you're visiting

12:54.298 --> 12:55.798
The family of a deceased victim,

12:55.925 --> 12:57.299
You need to hold a hat
over your chest.

12:57.385 --> 12:58.676
It shows you care.

12:58.803 --> 13:00.845
All I have is this crown
from our burger king lunch.

13:00.972 --> 13:02.263
Hat's a hat.

13:03.558 --> 13:06.350
How can I help you,
officer and your highness?

13:06.510 --> 13:10.187
Hi, yes. We're here with many
questions about your daughter.

13:10.273 --> 13:11.981
You know, the dead one?
You-you remember her?

13:12.066 --> 13:13.691
We'd love any details.

13:13.776 --> 13:15.818
Is this some sort of sick joke?

13:15.903 --> 13:17.153
I assure you it's not, ma'am.

13:17.238 --> 13:18.988
We're writing
a future hit novel

13:19.073 --> 13:20.156
Based on your daughter's murder.

13:20.283 --> 13:21.574
We just need to know who did it.

13:21.617 --> 13:24.285
And, between us, it'd be great
if one of you did.

13:24.370 --> 13:26.036
What is this?
What do you want?

13:26.122 --> 13:27.913
Did you know
jonbenét ramsey's dad

13:27.999 --> 13:30.541
Dated natalee holloway's mom?

13:30.626 --> 13:32.126
What does that have to do
with our case?

13:32.211 --> 13:34.044
Well, nothing,
it's just kind of weird, right?

13:34.130 --> 13:37.089
Do you happen to have
any grainy video footage

13:37.175 --> 13:40.176
Of her singing an emotional song
at a talent show?

13:40.261 --> 13:41.677
Maybe green day's
"time of your life"?

13:41.804 --> 13:44.680
That would really bust
this project wide open for us.

13:44.849 --> 13:46.807
You're both unwell.

13:48.269 --> 13:49.643
Well, that was a bust.

13:49.770 --> 13:52.354
Sorry, I've been holding this in
since burger king.

13:52.440 --> 13:54.315
Oh, seriously? You're just
gonna leave that there?

13:54.442 --> 13:57.109
These people have suffered
a terrible loss.

13:57.236 --> 13:59.361
At least cover it with leaves
or something.

13:59.530 --> 14:00.863
Ugh, fine.

14:04.535 --> 14:06.202
Joe, look.
I found something.

14:07.163 --> 14:09.580
-It's a key to a storage unit.
-How do you know that?

14:09.665 --> 14:12.124
Yeah, me and bonnie have been
doing a fun role-play thing

14:12.251 --> 14:14.168
Where she dresses up
like a sexy maid

14:14.253 --> 14:17.379
And then locks me in a storage
unit while guys come over.

14:17.465 --> 14:19.340
-Oh.
-Yeah, it's pretty kinky.

14:19.467 --> 14:22.426
I, uh, I play the role of
a sexy armoire,

14:22.512 --> 14:24.011
Waiting in another room.

14:24.096 --> 14:26.889
Sounds like she just wants you
out of the house for a while.

14:26.974 --> 14:29.308
Nah. No.

14:34.315 --> 14:36.357
It's okay, lois.
It's a big store.

14:36.484 --> 14:38.067
You may not even run into peter.

14:38.194 --> 14:41.111
Good morning.
How much are the mussels?

14:41.197 --> 14:43.364
$34 a month
at bally's total fitness.

14:43.449 --> 14:44.823
-(bell chimes)
-peter?

14:44.951 --> 14:46.492
Why are you
behind the fish counter?

14:46.536 --> 14:49.662
I got a promotion,
emphasis on the "otion."

14:49.789 --> 14:51.080
-(bell chimes)
-fine.

14:51.165 --> 14:52.790
What do you got that's fresh?

14:52.917 --> 14:54.333
Well, I got
a teenage son at home.

14:54.377 --> 14:56.252
-What a mouth on that kid.
-(bell chimes)

14:56.337 --> 14:59.088
That's it! You have
ruined groceries for me!

14:59.215 --> 15:01.549
Get the hell out of my store,
you imbecile!

15:01.634 --> 15:04.552
Um, excuse me, miss, did you
just yell at this employee?

15:04.679 --> 15:06.053
You're damn right I did.

15:06.138 --> 15:08.180
He has no business being here.

15:08.266 --> 15:10.808
This man is a member
of the stop 'n shop family.

15:10.935 --> 15:13.018
He has every business
being here.

15:13.104 --> 15:15.187
You, on the other hand,
will have to go.

15:15.314 --> 15:16.480
You're banned from the store.

15:16.566 --> 15:18.190
(chuckles nervously):
What? No.

15:18.317 --> 15:19.483
Y-you can't do this.

15:19.569 --> 15:21.360
I have shopped here
my whole life.

15:21.487 --> 15:23.445
Yes, we know.
If it's any consolation,

15:23.531 --> 15:25.239
You'll be in
the "in memoriam" section

15:25.366 --> 15:27.157
Of the grocery store oscars.

15:27.243 --> 15:29.034
("I will remember you"
by sarah mclachlan playing)

15:29.161 --> 15:34.999
♪<i> I will remember you</i> ♪

15:36.168 --> 15:41.213
-♪<i> will you remember me?</i> ♪
-(cheering)

15:42.466 --> 15:45.676
-♪<i> don't let your life...</i> ♪
-(man coughs)

15:45.803 --> 15:48.637
<i>Lois: No! No, no, no. You can't</i>
<i> put me after betty white.</i>

15:48.723 --> 15:51.015
Didn't brenda vaccaro die
or something?

15:51.100 --> 15:52.600
(gasps) no.

15:52.685 --> 15:55.936
I live here in aisle four
with the kotex tampons.

15:56.022 --> 15:58.063
(wheezing)

15:58.190 --> 15:59.940
Still more absorbent
than the leading brand.

16:00.067 --> 16:01.525
(wheezing)

17:38.616 --> 17:40.450
The worst part is,
I can't even go back

17:40.577 --> 17:42.327
To my favorite grocery store.

17:42.454 --> 17:44.912
I personally think
you should give peter a taste

17:45.081 --> 17:48.458
Of his own medicine and
get a job at his special place.

17:48.543 --> 17:50.460
The men's room at logan airport?

17:50.503 --> 17:52.253
No, the drunken clam.

17:52.339 --> 17:54.547
Oh, okay, 'cause he had
this one experience there

17:54.674 --> 17:56.299
That he still talks about
to this day,

17:56.384 --> 17:59.093
But that is an intriguing idea,
bonnie.

17:59.220 --> 18:00.553
I'm glad you think so.

18:00.638 --> 18:03.222
Well, as white women
in conversation,

18:03.308 --> 18:05.224
We're now obligated
to spend five minutes

18:05.310 --> 18:07.143
Talking about sedona, arizona.

18:07.270 --> 18:08.936
-Oh, I'd love to go.
-I know.

18:09.022 --> 18:12.357
My friend linda got a massage
there after her divorce.

18:12.484 --> 18:14.442
And my friend trish
bought a painting there.

18:14.527 --> 18:16.903
-Oh, we got to go.
-We got to go.

18:20.700 --> 18:23.618
Hey, you two haven't
seen peter, have you?

18:23.661 --> 18:25.661
Asking as a waitress
trying to teach him a lesson

18:25.747 --> 18:28.456
By working at his favorite
place, not as his wife.

18:28.541 --> 18:31.292
Whoa, check out the turd-cutter
on the new chick.

18:31.378 --> 18:33.294
That's right.
I work here now.

18:33.421 --> 18:35.421
I'm gonna be here all the time.

18:35.507 --> 18:37.382
Oh, how does it feel
to have someone invade

18:37.509 --> 18:39.133
Your special space?

18:39.219 --> 18:40.426
It feels great!

18:40.553 --> 18:42.136
Speaking of
invading special places,

18:42.222 --> 18:43.262
How about this?

18:43.390 --> 18:45.306
Hey, sweetie,
when do you get off work?

18:45.433 --> 18:47.683
Me and my wife are more friends
at this point than anything.

18:47.769 --> 18:49.227
Don't get me wrong,
she's a great gal,

18:49.312 --> 18:51.145
Raised my children,
but time takes its toll,

18:51.272 --> 18:52.313
You know what I mean?

18:52.440 --> 18:53.940
What? My wife and I have
an arrangement,

18:54.067 --> 18:56.651
So I'm not doing anything
wrong here, technically.

18:56.736 --> 18:58.694
Ah, well, this isn't working.

18:58.738 --> 19:01.030
If you want to meet me
in my car later,

19:01.116 --> 19:03.491
It's the one with
the "blue lives matter" sticker.

19:03.576 --> 19:06.702
But, like, not for cops,
it's for, it's for grover.

19:10.959 --> 19:12.458
Who's going in first?

19:12.544 --> 19:14.794
Kind of feels like you should
since you're a dog.

19:14.879 --> 19:16.045
Are you scared, joe?

19:16.172 --> 19:18.089
Would a scared person do this?

19:18.174 --> 19:21.050
-(screams)
-not so fast.

19:21.136 --> 19:23.219
<i> (serial</i> theme playing)

19:23.304 --> 19:24.720
Who is that?

19:24.806 --> 19:26.806
I'm guessing
it's the lady from<i> serial.</i>

19:26.891 --> 19:30.435
Oh, I certainly wouldn't
recognize a podcaster visually.

19:30.603 --> 19:33.104
-I'm sarah koenig.
-Big fan of your work.

19:33.189 --> 19:35.815
No one turns another person's
suffering into profit better.

19:35.942 --> 19:39.110
Listen up, I want this case
for my podcast,

19:39.195 --> 19:40.445
So you need to drop it.

19:40.530 --> 19:43.114
And if you don't,
I could make you disappear.

19:43.199 --> 19:45.441
We're sponsored
by casper mattresses.

19:45.493 --> 19:47.869
That wasn't a threat.
I have a code if you want it.

19:47.954 --> 19:50.121
Man:
Stand down, sarah.

19:50.206 --> 19:51.998
I'm keith morrison,

19:52.125 --> 19:54.750
And I want this case
for<i> dateline.</i>

19:54.878 --> 19:58.171
There are only a few hundred
unsolved murders left,

19:58.256 --> 20:01.966
And there's a million
true crime content creators.

20:02.093 --> 20:04.510
My grandson taught me that term.

20:04.637 --> 20:07.597
Who's "okay, boomer" now?

20:08.683 --> 20:11.559
We're npr's team
of women with lisps

20:11.644 --> 20:13.686
And names nobody's ever had,

20:13.771 --> 20:17.565
Like sylvia delgado-smith,
and audie takahashi o'shea.

20:17.692 --> 20:19.650
I'm chris hansen
from<i> to catch a predator,</i>

20:19.777 --> 20:21.819
And I'm just here
in case any of you

20:21.905 --> 20:23.154
Turn out to be pedophiles.

20:23.239 --> 20:25.448
Warm chocolate chip cookie,
anyone?

20:25.575 --> 20:28.159
No! I claimed this cold case
for<i> serial.</i>

20:28.244 --> 20:31.704
Not if I record a<i> dateline</i>
first.

20:32.207 --> 20:34.707
(all grunting)

20:40.840 --> 20:42.590
(choking)

20:42.675 --> 20:44.634
♪ ♪

20:47.138 --> 20:48.513
(screaming)

20:48.640 --> 20:50.556
(grunting)

20:58.274 --> 21:01.567
Please...
Rate and review my life.

21:01.653 --> 21:03.903
And someone take care of my dog

21:03.988 --> 21:06.948
You could usually hear
in the background of my podcast.

21:07.033 --> 21:08.991
(gasping)

21:09.160 --> 21:10.326
(grunting)

21:11.329 --> 21:14.372
A foggy night
at a storage unit in quahog.

21:14.415 --> 21:17.291
The sleepy little town of quahog

21:17.377 --> 21:21.087
Is usually all tucked in
by 10:00 p.M.

21:21.172 --> 21:23.214
(clamoring)

21:23.299 --> 21:25.174
You know what?
We're no better than them.

21:25.301 --> 21:27.051
We've been exploiting
the victim's life

21:27.136 --> 21:28.761
For our own personal gain.

21:28.846 --> 21:31.055
I-I think it's time for us
to abandon writing this book.

21:31.140 --> 21:35.268
Or... Maybe we set it to rap
lyrics and take it to broadway?

21:35.436 --> 21:37.270
I think we're done here.

21:38.439 --> 21:40.273
You know, joe,
even though it didn't work out,

21:40.400 --> 21:42.024
It was nice to spend
some time with someone

21:42.151 --> 21:43.651
Who actually believed
in my writing.

21:43.736 --> 21:47.530
Well, as someone who's never
read a book, I absolutely do.

21:51.160 --> 21:54.287
The waitress from the clam!
Holy crap, has lois seen you?!

21:54.372 --> 21:55.413
We really don't have
an arrangement.

21:55.540 --> 21:56.414
You got to get out of here!

21:56.541 --> 21:57.957
Oh, peter, enough.

21:58.042 --> 22:00.251
-What's the matter?
-You wouldn't understand.

22:00.295 --> 22:02.587
Okay.

22:03.965 --> 22:06.007
I'd get back in there, chief.

22:07.176 --> 22:09.719
(sighs) chris made me come back.

22:09.804 --> 22:11.971
Oh, honey,
the grocery store isn't just

22:12.056 --> 22:14.098
Where I buy food for the family.

22:14.183 --> 22:15.433
It's my escape.

22:15.518 --> 22:17.685
My refuge
from being pestered

22:17.770 --> 22:19.186
With dumb questions
from the kids,

22:19.272 --> 22:20.938
Or having to clean up
your messes.

22:21.065 --> 22:24.275
Sometimes, just a stroll
down the ethnic food aisle

22:24.360 --> 22:26.819
Makes me feel like
I'm in a north african bazaar.

22:26.946 --> 22:28.821
Yeah, I don't like the smells
on that aisle.

22:28.990 --> 22:32.158
-And I don't know,
it's hard to explain, but...
-There's more?!

22:32.243 --> 22:34.827
It's not just
a grocery store to me.

22:34.912 --> 22:36.996
There's a whole
community of people there

22:37.081 --> 22:38.497
Who feel like family.

22:38.583 --> 22:40.958
And now,
now I have nothing.

22:41.044 --> 22:45.171
Aw, lois, I'm so sorry
for ruining your happy place.

22:45.256 --> 22:47.006
And I'm gonna take care of it.

22:47.091 --> 22:49.425
Just like I've been taking care
of that egg since high school.

22:49.594 --> 22:52.386
Oh, my god, I forgot to pick
him up from soccer practice!

22:53.306 --> 22:56.349
Hey, do you need me
to call your yolks?

22:59.145 --> 23:00.728
Look, you got to let lois
come back.

23:00.813 --> 23:03.147
Please remove the ban.
She loves this place.

23:03.232 --> 23:04.398
I'm sorry, but I can't do that.

23:04.484 --> 23:06.859
She yelled at
a mentally-challenged person,

23:06.944 --> 23:07.985
And that's unforgivable.

23:08.154 --> 23:09.528
What?
I'm not mentally challenged.

23:09.614 --> 23:11.447
You're not?
But that's literally

23:11.532 --> 23:13.407
The only reason we hired you.

23:13.451 --> 23:16.911
Would a mentally challenged
person be able to do this?

23:21.125 --> 23:23.459
Your name tag says "big petey."

23:23.544 --> 23:25.544
(scoffs) why do you think
we all gather round

23:25.672 --> 23:27.296
And applaud you while you ride

23:27.340 --> 23:28.923
The coin-operated horse
out front?

23:29.008 --> 23:30.257
'cause I'm good at horses?

23:30.343 --> 23:32.677
Wow. (chuckles)
I really thought...

23:32.762 --> 23:35.054
You know, we don't let
all our employees insist

23:35.181 --> 23:37.932
The customers feel their muscles
after bagging their order.

23:37.975 --> 23:39.183
Right?

23:39.310 --> 23:40.351
Okay, fine.

23:40.478 --> 23:42.311
Lois can come back,
but you're fired.

23:42.397 --> 23:44.146
I need you to turn in
your gun and badge.

23:44.315 --> 23:46.732
Well, I guess
my work here is done.

23:46.859 --> 23:48.526
To the mickey-copter!

23:51.197 --> 23:52.321
See, disney?

23:52.407 --> 23:54.490
Nothing here
but respectful synergy.
